Text.Value: You are? Excellent! With someone like you on board, it can't fail!

EditorData.NodeContext: Pleased/excited for the player's involvement in the plan

Text.Value: Not quite what you were expecting from city life?
Good luck with that.
I'd like to be alone, thank you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad; mourning her friend (and trying not to show it)

Text.Value: I just wanted to get him back here safely. He was so scared - I could have done more to help him.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad/guilty at the loss of her friend as she feels somehow responsible

Text.Value: They. Are. Not. But trifle with them we will - Wulbren knows exactly where to hit them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Emphasis on the first three words - but then confident in her leader's plan

Text.Value: I don't know. I thought he would have calmed down after we got him away from that place, but... there's something else here disturbing him.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated she can't do more to help him

Text.Value: Look, once you've spoken to Wulbren we can talk, all right?

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly irritated at the player

Text.Value: I shouldn't say anything to you until you've spoken to Wulbren. He's very... particular.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wary of saying something they shouldn't to the player

Text.Value: And thank you for sticking with us - it certainly made things easier.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: THIS BRANCH DOESNT MAKE SENSE SINCE PLAYER DOES NOT HELP GNOMES ANY MORE
EditorData.NodeContext: Grateful

Text.Value: No thanks to you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Angry at player for not helping

Text.Value: I... I need a moment. Sorry.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad; she's thinking about Nickels

Text.Value: It was a close one - you almost didn't escape.
Almost makes you want to be back in Moonrise.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bitter sarcasm

Text.Value: Yeah, I saw that. Remind me to not rely on you in a crisis.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bitter at the player's cowardice

Text.Value: Wulbren's the one you should speak to - I'm just doing my part.

EditorData.NodeContext: Matter of fact (but definitely proud to be involved)

Text.Value: Steel Watchers certainly don't seem like things to be trifled with.
Thank Gaerdal we escaped that bloody Steel Watcher!

EditorData.NodeContext: Relieved

Text.Value: You've clearly never followed a true leader - when you do, you'll understand.

EditorData.NodeContext: Angry/defensive

Text.Value: Everything's lining up for the Ironhands, though - Wulbren's about to put his grand plan into action.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to perk herself back up; looking forward to the plan

Text.Value: I wish I had time to bury him. His ashes, I mean. But Wulbren's plan takes precedence.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad; trying to remain focused on Wulbren's plan

Text.Value: Well if someone hadn't almost gotten herself caught, it would've been a bit less dicey... but I suppose she tries her best.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly annoyed but then trying to be sympathetic

Text.Value: Don't worry - I'm going to be helping with Wulbren's plan.
We don't need luck - not with a plan like this one.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grimly confident

Text.Value: Can you blame me for not wanting to get involved?
I wish Nickels was here. Wulbren said his sacrifice was necessary, but... I miss him. And his rocks.

EditorData.NodeContext: Regretful/sad

Text.Value: Wulbren's boots must be the shiniest around with you here to lick them for him.
You are? Well, the sooner that's done with, the sooner I can give Nickels the burial he deserves. So thank you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad but grateful

Text.Value: What's wrong with Nickels? He seems pretty agitated.
I'm sorry, I panicked.
I've heard all about his plan - I think it sounds dangerous.
It looked like you had it under control.
I know - in fact, I'm going to be helping with it.
I'm sorry about Nickels.
Suppose not. But thought someone like you would've done more than turn tail and run.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bitter at the player's cowardice

Text.Value: We did - but we very nearly didn't.

EditorData.NodeContext: Well aware of how close a call it was

Text.Value: It's necessary. Besides, Wulbren wouldn't let anyone innocent get hurt.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sounds mostly convinced (but definitely not 100%)
